FL,495,460,260,120,000,100
PN,46902
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F469A1776957067
OL,3,CWhat happens if the largest party in
OL,4,CSenedd election falls short of a
OL,5,Cmajority?
OL,7,FHowever, today's poll puts them level
OL,8,Fwith Reform UK on 29%, with Dan
OL,9,FThomas's party projected to be the
OL,10,Flargest party by just a single seat.
OL,12,FIt suggests that this year's election
OL,13,Fwill be by far and away the most
OL,14,Fcompetitive of the devolved era, and
OL,15,Fright now it feels far too close to
OL,16,Fcall.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G2/9
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
