PN,46904
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F469A1776957067
OL,3,CWhat happens if the largest party in
OL,4,CSenedd election falls short of a
OL,5,Cmajority?
OL,7,FParticipants in the poll were also
OL,8,Fasked to list the parties they did NOT
OL,9,Fwant to see form the next Welsh
OL,10,FGovernment and 49% said Reform UK.
OL,11,FThis is way ahead of the Conservatives
OL,12,F(39%), who have traditionally played
OL,13,Fthe role of electoral pantomime
OL,14,Fvillains in many parts of Wales, and a
OL,15,FLabour Party (37%) currently suffering
OL,16,Fa severe backlash after 27 years in
OL,17,Fpower.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G4/9
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
