OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F469A1776957067
OL,3,CWhat happens if the largest party in
OL,4,CSenedd election falls short of a
OL,5,Cmajority?
OL,7,FThis emphasises a trend we have
OL,8,Fconsistently seen when speaking to the
OL,9,Fpublic in the build-up to this
OL,10,Felection. Reform UK have a sizeable
OL,11,Fand energised base of passionate
OL,12,Fsupporters who are desperate to see
OL,13,FWales turn light blue on May 7, and
OL,14,Fthis poll suggests that group may very
OL,15,Fwell be big enough to make them the
OL,16,Flargest party in Cardiff Bay.
OL,18,FHowever, the party polarises opinion
OL,19,Fand wherever we go, we tend to find a
OL,20,Fnumber of people who tell us they want
OL,21,Fanyone BUT Reform UK in power.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G5/9
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
