OL,3,CWhat happens if the largest party in
OL,4,CSenedd election falls short of a
OL,5,Cmajority?
OL,7,FWelsh politics is poised for radical
OL,8,Fchange after more than a century of
OL,9,FLabour dominance, but with the two
OL,10,Fleading parties neck and neck and well
OL,11,Fshort of a majority, the question of
OL,12,Fwho governs Wales may depend on which
OL,13,Fparties are able to set differences
OL,14,Faside and work together.
OL,16,FOf course, there are still 16 days
OL,17,Fleft for every party to make their
OL,18,Fcase to the electorate, meaning it
OL,19,Fcould all change by the time polling
OL,20,Fstations close on May 7.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G8/9
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
